  S V      O 
  John ate the yam 
 
In this simple sentence, John is the subject represented by S, ate is the 
verb represented by V and the yam is object of the sentence represented 
by O. In the sentence, there is no inversion or interchange of the yam 
and John. Thus we will say the sentence John ate the yam is in the 
active voice. 
 
